Reasoning: The paper deals with statistical estimators and their bias when evaluated on a baseline model rather than the true model. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of concentration inequalities and moment generating functions suggests a focus on probability theory and statistics, which could place the paper in sub-categories such as artificial intelligence (cs.AI), statistics (cs.ST), or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
